title: Gross domestic product ( GDP ) growth rate in Finland 2024
yAxis: GDP growth compared to previous year
summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing GDP growth compared to previous year, containing a total of 11 data points.
Overall GDP growth compared to previous year has increased over the Year.
GDP growth compared to previous year is roughly constant from 2014 to 2015, gradually increasing from 2015 to 2016, and lastly roughly constant from 2016 to 2024.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 2015 and 2016.
Maximum GDP growth compared to previous year, about 3.04 was reported at Year 2017
The lowest GDP growth compared to previous year, of value 0.5 was reported at Year 2015
